{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.9",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 9,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 9",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 9 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:2",
      "text": "I know of a truth that it is so: for how shall a mortal man be just before the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:3",
      "text": "For if he would enter into judgement with him, God would not hearken to him, so that he should answer to one of his charges of a thousand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:4",
      "text": "For he is wise in mind, and mighty, and great: who has hardened himself against him and endured?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:5",
      "text": "Who wears out the mountains, and men know it not: who overturns them in anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:6",
      "text": "Who shakes the earth under heaven from its foundations, and its pillars totter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:7",
      "text": "Who commands the sun, and it rises not; and he seals up the stars.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:8",
      "text": "Who alone has stretched out the heavens, and walks on the sea as on firm ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:9",
      "text": "Who makes Pleias, and Hesperus, and Arcturus, and the chambers of the south.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:10",
      "text": "Who does great and unsearchable things; glorious also and excellent things, innumerable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:11",
      "text": "If ever he should go beyond me, I shall not see him: if he should pass by me, neither thus have I known it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:12",
      "text": "If he would take away, who shall turn him back? or who shall say to him, What hast thou done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:13",
      "text": "For if he has turned away his anger, the whales under heaven have stooped under him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:14",
      "text": "Oh then that he would hearken to me, or judge my cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:15",
      "text": "For though I be righteous, he will not hearken to me: I will intreat his judgement.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:16",
      "text": "And if I should call and he should not hearken, I cannot believe that he has listened to my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:17",
      "text": "Let him not crush me with a dark storm: but he has made by bruises many without cause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:18",
      "text": "For he suffers me not to take breath, but he has filled me with bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:19",
      "text": "For indeed he is strong in power: who then shall resist his judgement?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:20",
      "text": "For though I should seem righteous, my mouth will be profane: and though I should seem blameless, I shall be proved perverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:21",
      "text": "For even if I have sinned, I know it not in my soul: but my life is taken away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:22",
      "text": "Wherefore I said, Wrath slays the great and mighty man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:23",
      "text": "For the worthless die, but the righteous are laughed to scorn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:24",
      "text": "For they are delivered into the hands of the unrighteous man: he covers the faces of the judges of the earth: but if it be not he, who is it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:25",
      "text": "But my life is swifter than a post: my days have fled away, and they knew it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:26",
      "text": "Or again, is there a trace of their path left by ships? or is there one of the flying eagle as it seeks its prey?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:27",
      "text": "And if I should say, I will forget to speak, I will bow down my face and groan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:28",
      "text": "I quake in all my limbs, for I know that thou wilt not leave me alone as innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:29",
      "text": "But since I am ungodly, why have I not died?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:30",
      "text": "For if I should wash myself with snow, and purge myself with pure hands,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:31",
      "text": "thou hadst thoroughly plunged me in filth, and my garment had abhorred me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:32",
      "text": "For thou art not man like me, with whom I could contend, that we might come together to judgement.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:33",
      "text": "Would that he our mediator were present, and a reprover, and one who should hear the cause between both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:34",
      "text": "Let him remove his rod from me, and let not his fear terrify me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.9.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:35",
      "text": "so shall I not be afraid, but I will speak: for I am not thus conscious of guilt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
